81  template <typename SrcChar, typename DestChar>
82  V8_INLINE void Append(SrcChar c) {
83  DCHECK_EQ(encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING, sizeof(DestChar) == 1);
84  if (sizeof(DestChar) == 1) {
85  DCHECK_EQ(String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING, encoding_);
86  one_byte_ptr_[current_index_++] = c;
87  } else {
88  DCHECK_EQ(String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING, encoding_);
89  // Make sure to use unsigned extension even when SrcChar == char.
90  two_byte_ptr_[current_index_++] =
91  static_cast<std::make_unsigned_t<SrcChar>>(c);
92  }
93  if V8_UNLIKELY (current_index_ == part_length_) Extend();
94  }
95 
96  V8_INLINE void AppendCharacter(uint8_t c) {
97  if (encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING) {
98  Append<uint8_t, uint8_t>(c);
99  } else {
100  Append<uint8_t, base::uc16>(c);
101  }
102  }
103 
104  template <size_t N>
105  V8_INLINE void AppendCStringLiteral(const char (&literal)[N]) {
106  // Note that the literal contains the zero char.
107  constexpr size_t length = N - 1;
108  static_assert(length > 0);
109  if (length == 1) return AppendCharacter(literal[0]);
110  if (encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING && CurrentPartCanFit(N)) {
111  const uint8_t* chars = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(literal);
112  CopyChars<uint8_t, uint8_t>(one_byte_ptr_ + current_index_, chars,
113  length);
114  current_index_ += length;
115  if (current_index_ == part_length_) Extend();
116  DCHECK(HasValidCurrentIndex());
117  return;
118  }
119  return AppendCString(literal);
120  }
121 
122  template <typename SrcChar>
123  V8_INLINE void AppendCString(const SrcChar* s) {
124  if (encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING) {
125  while (*s != '\0') Append<SrcChar, uint8_t>(*s++);
126  } else {
127  while (*s != '\0') Append<SrcChar, base::uc16>(*s++);
128  }
129  }
130 
131  template <typename SrcChar>
132  V8_INLINE void AppendString(std::basic_string_view<SrcChar> s) {
133  if (encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING) {
134  for (SrcChar c : s) Append<SrcChar, uint8_t>(c);
135  } else {
136  for (SrcChar c : s) Append<SrcChar, base::uc16>(c);
137  }
138  }
139 
140  V8_INLINE bool CurrentPartCanFit(size_t length) {
141  return part_length_ - current_index_ > length;
142  }
143 
144  // We make a rough estimate to find out if the current string can be
145  // serialized without allocating a new string part. The worst case length of
146  // an escaped character is 6. Shifting the remaining string length left by 3
147  // is a more pessimistic estimate, but faster to calculate.
148  V8_INLINE bool EscapedLengthIfCurrentPartFits(size_t length) {
149  if (length > kMaxPartLength) return false;
150  static_assert(kMaxPartLength <= (String::kMaxLength >> 3));
151  // This shift will not overflow because length is already less than the
152  // maximum part length.
153  return CurrentPartCanFit(length << 3);
154  }
155 
156  void AppendStringByCopy(Tagged<String> string, size_t length,
157  const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
158  DCHECK_EQ(length, string->length());
159  DCHECK(encoding_ == String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING ||
160  (string->IsFlat() &&
161  String::IsOneByteRepresentationUnderneath(string)));
162  DCHECK(CurrentPartCanFit(length + 1));
163  if (encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING) {
164  if (String::IsOneByteRepresentationUnderneath(string)) {
165  CopyChars<uint8_t, uint8_t>(
166  one_byte_ptr_ + current_index_,
167  string->GetCharVector<uint8_t>(no_gc).begin(), length);
168  } else {
169  ChangeEncoding();
170  CopyChars<uint16_t, uint16_t>(
171  two_byte_ptr_ + current_index_,
172  string->GetCharVector<uint16_t>(no_gc).begin(), length);
173  }
174  } else {
175  if (String::IsOneByteRepresentationUnderneath(string)) {
176  CopyChars<uint8_t, uint16_t>(
177  two_byte_ptr_ + current_index_,
178  string->GetCharVector<uint8_t>(no_gc).begin(), length);
179  } else {
180  CopyChars<uint16_t, uint16_t>(
181  two_byte_ptr_ + current_index_,
182  string->GetCharVector<uint16_t>(no_gc).begin(), length);
183  }
184  }
185  current_index_ += length;
186  DCHECK(current_index_ <= part_length_);
187  }
188 
189  V8_NOINLINE void AppendString(Handle<String> string_handle) {
190  {
191  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
192  Tagged<String> string = *string_handle;
193  const bool representation_ok =
194  encoding_ == String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING ||
195  (string->IsFlat() &&
196  String::IsOneByteRepresentationUnderneath(string));
197  if (representation_ok) {
198  size_t length = string->length();
199  while (!CurrentPartCanFit(length + 1)) {
200  Extend();
201  if (V8_UNLIKELY(overflowed_)) return;
202  }
203  AppendStringByCopy(string, length, no_gc);
204  return;
205  }
206  }
207  SerializeString<true>(string_handle);
208  }
209 
210  template <typename SrcChar>
211  void AppendSubstringByCopy(const SrcChar* src, size_t count) {
212  DCHECK(CurrentPartCanFit(count + 1));
213  if (encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING) {
214  if (sizeof(SrcChar) == 1) {
215  CopyChars<SrcChar, uint8_t>(one_byte_ptr_ + current_index_, src, count);
216  } else {
217  ChangeEncoding();
218  CopyChars<SrcChar, base::uc16>(two_byte_ptr_ + current_index_, src,
219  count);
220  }
221  } else {
222  CopyChars<SrcChar, base::uc16>(two_byte_ptr_ + current_index_, src,
223  count);
224  }
225  current_index_ += count;
226  DCHECK_LE(current_index_, part_length_);
227  }
228 
229  template <typename SrcChar>
230  V8_NOINLINE void AppendSubstring(const SrcChar* src, size_t from, size_t to) {
231  if (from == to) return;
232  DCHECK_LT(from, to);
233  size_t count = to - from;
234  while (!CurrentPartCanFit(count + 1)) {
235  Extend();
236  if (V8_UNLIKELY(overflowed_)) return;
237  }
238  AppendSubstringByCopy(src + from, count);
239  }

282  template <typename DestChar>
283  class NoExtendBuilder {
284  public:
285  NoExtendBuilder(DestChar* start, size_t* current_index)
286  : current_index_(current_index), start_(start), cursor_(start) {}
287  ~NoExtendBuilder() { *current_index_ += cursor_ - start_; }
288 
289  V8_INLINE void Append(DestChar c) { *(cursor_++) = c; }
290  V8_INLINE void AppendCString(const char* s) {
291  const uint8_t* u = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(s);
292  while (*u != '\0') Append(*(u++));
293  }
294  V8_INLINE void AppendString(std::string_view str) {
295  AppendChars(
296  base::Vector<const uint8_t>(
297  reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(str.data()), str.length()),
298  str.length());
299  }
300 
301  // Appends all of the chars from the provided span, but only increases the
302  // cursor by `length`. This allows oversizing the span to the nearest
303  // convenient multiple, allowing CopyChars to run slightly faster.
304  V8_INLINE void AppendChars(base::Vector<const uint8_t> chars,
305  size_t length) {
306  DCHECK_GE(chars.size(), length);
307  CopyChars(cursor_, chars.begin(), chars.size());
308  cursor_ += length;
309  }
310 
311  template <typename SrcChar>
312  V8_INLINE void AppendSubstring(const SrcChar* src, size_t from, size_t to) {
313  if (from == to) return;
314  DCHECK_LT(from, to);
315  size_t count = to - from;
316  CopyChars(cursor_, src + from, count);
317  cursor_ += count;
318  }
319 
320  private:
321  size_t* current_index_;
322  DestChar* start_;
323  DestChar* cursor_;
324  };

326  // A cache of recently seen property keys which were simple. Simple means:
327  //
328  // - Internalized, sequential, one-byte string
329  // - Contains no characters which need escaping
330  //
331  // This can be helpful because it's common for JSON to have lists of similar
332  // objects. Since property keys are internalized, we will see identical key
333  // pointers again and again, and we can use a fast path to copy those keys to
334  // the output. However, strings can be externalized any time JS runs, so the
335  // caller is responsible for checking whether a string is still the expected
336  // type. This cache is cleared on GC, since the GC could move those strings.
337  // Using Handles for the cache has been tried, but is too expensive to set up
338  // when JSON.stringify is called for tiny inputs.
339  class SimplePropertyKeyCache {
340  public:
341  explicit SimplePropertyKeyCache(Isolate* isolate) : isolate_(isolate) {
342  Clear();
343  isolate->main_thread_local_heap()->AddGCEpilogueCallback(
344  UpdatePointersCallback, this);
345  }
346 
347  ~SimplePropertyKeyCache() {
348  isolate_->main_thread_local_heap()->RemoveGCEpilogueCallback(
349  UpdatePointersCallback, this);
350  }
351 
352  void TryInsert(Tagged<String> string) {
353  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate_);
354  if (string->map() == roots.internalized_one_byte_string_map()) {
355  keys_[GetIndex(string)] = MaybeCompress(string);
356  }
357  }
358 
359  bool Contains(Tagged<String> string) {
360  return keys_[GetIndex(string)] == MaybeCompress(string);
361  }
362 
363  private:
364  size_t GetIndex(Tagged<String> string) {
365  // Short strings are 16 bytes long in pointer-compression builds, so the
366  // lower four bits of the pointer may not provide much entropy.
367  return (string.ptr() >> 4) & kIndexMask;
368  }
369 
370  Tagged_t MaybeCompress(Tagged<String> string) {
371  return COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL
372  ? V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(string.ptr())
373  : static_cast<Tagged_t>(string.ptr());
374  }
375 
376  void Clear() { MemsetTagged(keys_, Smi::zero(), kSize); }
377 
378  static void UpdatePointersCallback(void* cache) {
379  reinterpret_cast<SimplePropertyKeyCache*>(cache)->Clear();
380  }
381 
382  static constexpr size_t kSizeBits = 6;
383  static constexpr size_t kSize = 1 << kSizeBits;
384  static constexpr size_t kIndexMask = kSize - 1;
385 
386  Isolate* isolate_;
387  Tagged_t keys_[kSize];
388  };

508 template <>

510  // https://tc39.github.io/ecma262/#table-json-single-character-escapes
511  return JsonDoNotEscapeFlagTable[c];

514 template <>
515 constexpr bool DoNotEscape(uint16_t c) {
516  // https://tc39.github.io/ecma262/#table-json-single-character-escapes
517  return (c >= 0x20 && c <= 0x21) ||
518  (c >= 0x23 && c != 0x5C && (c < 0xD800 || c > 0xDFFF));
519 }
520 
521 // Checks if characters need escaping in a packed input (4 bytes in uint32_t).
522 constexpr bool NeedsEscape(uint32_t input) {
523  constexpr uint32_t mask_0x20 = 0x20202020u;
524  constexpr uint32_t mask_0x22 = 0x22222222u;
525  constexpr uint32_t mask_0x5c = 0x5C5C5C5Cu;
526  constexpr uint32_t mask_0x01 = 0x01010101u;
527  constexpr uint32_t mask_msb = 0x80808080u;
528  // Escape control characters (< 0x20).
529  const uint32_t has_lt_0x20 = input - mask_0x20;
530  // Escape double quotation mark (0x22).
531  const uint32_t has_0x22 = (input ^ mask_0x22) - mask_0x01;
532  // Escape backslash (0x5C).
533  const uint32_t has_0x5c = (input ^ mask_0x5c) - mask_0x01;
534  // Chars >= 0x7F don't need escaping.
535  const uint32_t result_mask = ~input & mask_msb;
536  const uint32_t result = ((has_lt_0x20 | has_0x22 | has_0x5c) & result_mask);
537  return result != 0;
538 }
539 // LINT.ThenChange(/src/objects/string.cc:StringDoesNotContainEscapeCharacters)

541 template <typename SrcChar>
542  requires(sizeof(SrcChar) == sizeof(uint8_t))
543 bool DoNotEscape(const SrcChar* chars, size_t length,
544  const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
545  bool no_escape = true;
546  using PackedT = uint32_t;
547  static constexpr size_t stride = sizeof(PackedT);
548  size_t i = 0;
549  for (; i + (stride - 1) < length; i += stride) {
550  PackedT packed = *reinterpret_cast<const PackedT*>(chars + i);
551  if (V8_UNLIKELY(NeedsEscape(packed))) break;
552  }
553  for (; i < length; i++) {
554  no_escape = no_escape && DoNotEscape(chars[i]);
555  }
556  return no_escape;
557 }

559 bool IsFastKey(Tagged<String> key, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
560  return key->DispatchToSpecificType(
561  absl::Overload{[&](Tagged<SeqOneByteString> str) {
562  const uint8_t* chars = str->GetChars(no_gc);
563  return DoNotEscape(chars, str->length(), no_gc);
564  },
565  [&](Tagged<ExternalOneByteString> str) {
566  const uint8_t* chars = str->GetChars();
567  return DoNotEscape(chars, str->length(), no_gc);
568  },
569  [&](Tagged<String> str) { return false; }});
570 }

572 bool CanFastSerializeJSArray(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSArray> object) {
573  // If the no elements protector is intact, Array.prototype and
574  // Object.prototype are guaranteed to not have elements in any native context.
575  if (!Protectors::IsNoElementsIntact(isolate)) return false;
576  Tagged<Map> map = object->map(isolate);
577  Tagged<NativeContext> native_context = map->map(isolate)->native_context();
578  Tagged<HeapObject> proto = map->prototype();
579  return native_context->GetNoCell(Context::INITIAL_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_INDEX) ==
580  proto;
581 }

583 V8_INLINE bool CanFastSerializeJSObject(Tagged<JSObject> raw_object,
584  Isolate* isolate) {
585  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
586  if (IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(raw_object->map())) return false;
587  if (!raw_object->HasFastProperties()) return false;
588  auto roots = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate);
589  auto elements = raw_object->elements();
590  return elements == roots.empty_fixed_array() ||
591  elements == roots.empty_slow_element_dictionary();
592 }

604  stack_nesting_level_(0),
605  overflowed_(false),

613 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> JsonStringifier::Stringify(Handle<JSAny> object,
614  Handle<JSAny> replacer,
615  Handle<Object> gap) {
616  if (!InitializeReplacer(replacer)) {
617  CHECK(isolate_->has_exception());
618  return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>();
619  }
620  if (!IsUndefined(*gap, isolate_) && !InitializeGap(gap)) {
621  CHECK(isolate_->has_exception());
622  return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>();
623  }
624  Result result = SerializeObject(object);
625  if (result == NEED_STACK) {
626  indent_ = 0;
627  current_index_ = 0;
628  result = SerializeObject(object);
629  }
630  if (result == UNCHANGED) return factory()->undefined_value();
631  if (result == SUCCESS) {
632  if (overflowed_ || current_index_ > String::kMaxLength) {
633  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate_, NewInvalidStringLengthError());
634  }
635  if (encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING) {
636  return isolate_->factory()
637  ->NewStringFromOneByte(base::OneByteVector(
638  reinterpret_cast<char*>(one_byte_ptr_), current_index_))
639  .ToHandleChecked();
640  } else {
641  return isolate_->factory()->NewStringFromTwoByte(
642  base::Vector<const base::uc16>(two_byte_ptr_, current_index_));
643  }
644  }
645  DCHECK(result == EXCEPTION);
646  CHECK(isolate_->has_exception());
647  return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>();
648 }
649 
650 bool JsonStringifier::InitializeReplacer(Handle<JSAny> replacer) {
651  DCHECK(property_list_.is_null());
652  DCHECK(replacer_function_.is_null());
653  Maybe<bool> is_array = Object::IsArray(replacer);
654  if (is_array.IsNothing()) return false;
655  if (is_array.FromJust()) {
656  HandleScope handle_scope(isolate_);
657  Handle<OrderedHashSet> set = factory()->NewOrderedHashSet();
658  DirectHandle<Object> length_obj;
659  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
660  isolate_, length_obj,
661  Object::GetLengthFromArrayLike(isolate_, Cast<JSReceiver>(replacer)),
662  false);
663  uint32_t length;
664  if (!Object::ToUint32(*length_obj, &length)) length = kMaxUInt32;
665  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
666  Handle<Object> element;
667  Handle<String> key;
668  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
669  isolate_, element, Object::GetElement(isolate_, replacer, i), false);
670  if (IsNumber(*element) || IsString(*element)) {
671  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
672  isolate_, key, Object::ToString(isolate_, element), false);
673  } else if (IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*element)) {
674  DirectHandle<Object> value(Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(element)->value(),
675  isolate_);
676  if (IsNumber(*value) || IsString(*value)) {
677  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
678  isolate_, key, Object::ToString(isolate_, element), false);
679  }
680  }
681  if (key.is_null()) continue;
682  // Object keys are internalized, so do it here.
683  key = factory()->InternalizeString(key);
684  MaybeHandle<OrderedHashSet> set_candidate =
685  OrderedHashSet::Add(isolate_, set, key);
686  if (!set_candidate.ToHandle(&set)) {
687  CHECK(isolate_->has_exception());
688  return false;
689  }
690  }
691  property_list_ = OrderedHashSet::ConvertToKeysArray(
692  isolate_, set, GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers);
693  property_list_ = handle_scope.CloseAndEscape(property_list_);
694  } else if (IsCallable(*replacer)) {
695  replacer_function_ = Cast<JSReceiver>(replacer);
696  }
697  return true;
698 }
699 
700 bool JsonStringifier::InitializeGap(Handle<Object> gap) {
701  DCHECK_NULL(gap_);
702  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
703  if (IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*gap)) {
704  DirectHandle<Object> value(Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(gap)->value(),
705  isolate_);
706  if (IsString(*value)) {
707  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate_, gap,
708  Object::ToString(isolate_, gap), false);
709  } else if (IsNumber(*value)) {
710  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate_, gap,
711  Object::ToNumber(isolate_, gap), false);
712  }
713  }
714 
715  if (IsString(*gap)) {
716  auto gap_string = Cast<String>(gap);
717  if (gap_string->length() > 0) {
718  uint32_t gap_length = std::min(gap_string->length(), 10u);
719  gap_ = NewArray<base::uc16>(gap_length + 1);
720  String::WriteToFlat(*gap_string, gap_, 0, gap_length);
721  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < gap_length; i++) {
722  if (gap_[i] > String::kMaxOneByteCharCode) {
723  ChangeEncoding();
724  break;
725  }
726  }
727  gap_[gap_length] = '\0';
728  }
729  } else if (IsNumber(*gap)) {
730  double value = std::min(Object::NumberValue(*gap), 10.0);
731  if (value > 0) {
732  uint32_t gap_length = DoubleToUint32(value);
733  gap_ = NewArray<base::uc16>(gap_length + 1);
734  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < gap_length; i++) gap_[i] = ' ';
735  gap_[gap_length] = '\0';
736  }
737  }
738  return true;
739 }

741 MaybeHandle<JSAny> JsonStringifier::ApplyToJsonFunction(
742  Handle<JSAny> object, DirectHandle<Object> key) {
743  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
744 
745  // Retrieve toJSON function. The LookupIterator automatically handles
746  // the ToObject() equivalent ("GetRoot") if {object} is a BigInt.
747  DirectHandle<Object> fun;
748  LookupIterator it(isolate_, object, factory()->toJSON_string(),
749  LookupIterator::PROTOTYPE_CHAIN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
750  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate_, fun, Object::GetProperty(&it));
751  if (!IsCallable(*fun)) return object;
752 
753  // Call toJSON function.
754  if (IsSmi(*key)) key = factory()->SmiToString(Cast<Smi>(*key));
755  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {key};
756  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate_, object,
757  Cast<JSAny>(Execution::Call(
758  isolate_, fun, object, base::VectorOf(args))));
759  return scope.CloseAndEscape(object);
760 }

762 MaybeHandle<JSAny> JsonStringifier::ApplyReplacerFunction(
763  Handle<JSAny> value, DirectHandle<Object> key,
764  DirectHandle<Object> initial_holder) {
765  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
766  if (IsSmi(*key)) key = factory()->SmiToString(Cast<Smi>(*key));
767  DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {key, value};
768  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> holder = CurrentHolder(value, initial_holder);
769  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
770  isolate_, value,
771  Cast<JSAny>(Execution::Call(isolate_, replacer_function_, holder,
772  base::VectorOf(args))));
773  return scope.CloseAndEscape(value);
774 }
775 
776 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> JsonStringifier::CurrentHolder(
777  DirectHandle<Object> value, DirectHandle<Object> initial_holder) {
778  if (stack_.empty()) {
779  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder =
780  factory()->NewJSObject(isolate_->object_function());
781  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate_, holder, factory()->empty_string(),
782  initial_holder, NONE);
783  return holder;
784  } else {
785  return DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(Cast<JSReceiver>(*stack_.back().second),
786  isolate_);
787  }
788 }
789 
790 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::StackPush(Handle<Object> object,
791  Handle<Object> key) {
792  if (!need_stack_) {
793  ++stack_nesting_level_;
794  if V8_UNLIKELY (stack_nesting_level_ > 10) {
795  need_stack_ = true;
796  return NEED_STACK;
797  }
798  return SUCCESS;
799  }
800  StackLimitCheck check(isolate_);
801  if (check.HasOverflowed()) {
802  isolate_->StackOverflow();
803  return EXCEPTION;
804  }
805 
806  {
807  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
808  Tagged<Object> raw_obj = *object;
809  size_t size = stack_.size();
810  for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
811  if (*stack_[i].second == raw_obj) {
812  AllowGarbageCollection allow_to_return_error;
813  Handle<String> circle_description =
814  ConstructCircularStructureErrorMessage(key, i);
815  DirectHandle<Object> error = factory()->NewTypeError(
816  MessageTemplate::kCircularStructure, circle_description);
817  isolate_->Throw(*error);
818  return EXCEPTION;
819  }
820  }
821  }
822  stack_.emplace_back(key, object);
823  return SUCCESS;
824 }
825 
826 void JsonStringifier::StackPop() {
827  if V8_LIKELY (!need_stack_) {
828  --stack_nesting_level_;
829  return;
830  }
831  stack_.pop_back();
832 }

834 class CircularStructureMessageBuilder {
835  public:
836  explicit CircularStructureMessageBuilder(Isolate* isolate)
837  : builder_(isolate) {}
838 
839  void AppendStartLine(DirectHandle<Object> start_object) {
840  builder_.AppendCString(kStartPrefix);
841  builder_.AppendCStringLiteral("starting at object with constructor ");
842  AppendConstructorName(start_object);
843  }
844 
845  void AppendNormalLine(DirectHandle<Object> key, DirectHandle<Object> object) {
846  builder_.AppendCString(kLinePrefix);
847  AppendKey(key);
848  builder_.AppendCStringLiteral(" -> object with constructor ");
849  AppendConstructorName(object);
850  }
851 
852  void AppendClosingLine(DirectHandle<Object> closing_key) {
853  builder_.AppendCString(kEndPrefix);
854  AppendKey(closing_key);
855  builder_.AppendCStringLiteral(" closes the circle");
856  }
857 
858  void AppendEllipsis() {
859  builder_.AppendCString(kLinePrefix);
860  builder_.AppendCStringLiteral("...");
861  }
862 
863  MaybeDirectHandle<String> Finish() { return builder_.Finish(); }
864 
865  private:
866  void AppendConstructorName(DirectHandle<Object> object) {
867  builder_.AppendCharacter('\'');
868  DirectHandle<String> constructor_name = JSReceiver::GetConstructorName(
869  builder_.isolate(), Cast<JSReceiver>(object));
870  builder_.AppendString(constructor_name);
871  builder_.AppendCharacter('\'');
872  }
873 
874  // A key can either be a string, the empty string or a Smi.
875  void AppendKey(DirectHandle<Object> key) {
876  if (IsSmi(*key)) {
877  builder_.AppendCStringLiteral("index ");
878  AppendSmi(Cast<Smi>(*key));
879  return;
880  }
881 
882  CHECK(IsString(*key));
883  DirectHandle<String> key_as_string = Cast<String>(key);
884  if (key_as_string->length() == 0) {
885  builder_.AppendCStringLiteral("<anonymous>");
886  } else {
887  builder_.AppendCStringLiteral("property '");
888  builder_.AppendString(key_as_string);
889  builder_.AppendCharacter('\'');
890  }
891  }
892 
893  void AppendSmi(Tagged<Smi> smi) {
894  static_assert(Smi::kMaxValue <= 2147483647);
895  static_assert(Smi::kMinValue >= -2147483648);
896  // sizeof(string) includes \0.
897  static constexpr uint32_t kBufferSize = sizeof("-2147483648") - 1;
898  char chars[kBufferSize];
899  base::Vector<char> buffer(chars, kBufferSize);
900  builder_.AppendString(IntToStringView(smi.value(), buffer));
901  }
902 
903  IncrementalStringBuilder builder_;
904  static constexpr const char* kStartPrefix = "\n --> ";
905  static constexpr const char* kEndPrefix = "\n --- ";
906  static constexpr const char* kLinePrefix = "\n | ";
907 };
908 
909 Handle<String> JsonStringifier::ConstructCircularStructureErrorMessage(
910  DirectHandle<Object> last_key, size_t start_index) {
911  DCHECK(start_index < stack_.size());
912  CircularStructureMessageBuilder builder(isolate_);
913 
914  // We track the index to be printed next for better readability.
915  size_t index = start_index;
916  const size_t stack_size = stack_.size();
917 
918  builder.AppendStartLine(stack_[index++].second);
919 
920  // Append a maximum of kCircularErrorMessagePrefixCount normal lines.
921  const size_t prefix_end =
922  std::min(stack_size, index + kCircularErrorMessagePrefixCount);
923  for (; index < prefix_end; ++index) {
924  builder.AppendNormalLine(stack_[index].first, stack_[index].second);
925  }
926 
927  // If the circle consists of too many objects, we skip them and just
928  // print an ellipsis.
929  if (stack_size > index + kCircularErrorMessagePostfixCount) {
930  builder.AppendEllipsis();
931  }
932 
933  // Since we calculate the postfix lines from the back of the stack,
934  // we have to ensure that lines are not printed twice.
935  index = std::max(index, stack_size - kCircularErrorMessagePostfixCount);
936  for (; index < stack_size; ++index) {
937  builder.AppendNormalLine(stack_[index].first, stack_[index].second);
938  }
939 
940  builder.AppendClosingLine(last_key);
941 
942  Handle<String> result;
943  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate_, result,
944  indirect_handle(builder.Finish(), isolate_),
945  factory()->empty_string());
946  return result;
947 }

949 bool MayHaveInterestingProperties(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSReceiver> object) {
950  for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, object, kStartAtReceiver);
951  !iter.IsAtEnd(); iter.Advance()) {
952  if (iter.GetCurrent()->map()->may_have_interesting_properties()) {
953  return true;
954  }
955  }
956  return false;
957 }

959 template <bool deferred_string_key>
960 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::Serialize_(Handle<JSAny> object,
961  bool comma,
962  Handle<Object> key) {
963  StackLimitCheck interrupt_check(isolate_);
964  if (interrupt_check.InterruptRequested() &&
965  IsException(isolate_->stack_guard()->HandleInterrupts(), isolate_)) {
966  return EXCEPTION;
967  }
968 
969  DirectHandle<JSAny> initial_value = object;
970  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate_);
971  if (!IsSmi(*object)) {
972  InstanceType instance_type =
973  Cast<HeapObject>(*object)->map(cage_base)->instance_type();
974  if ((InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(instance_type) &&
975  MayHaveInterestingProperties(isolate_, Cast<JSReceiver>(*object))) ||
976  InstanceTypeChecker::IsBigInt(instance_type)) {
977  if (!need_stack_ && stack_nesting_level_ > 0) {
978  need_stack_ = true;
979  return NEED_STACK;
980  }
981  need_stack_ = true;
982  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
983  isolate_, object, ApplyToJsonFunction(object, key), EXCEPTION);
984  }
985  }
986  if (!replacer_function_.is_null()) {
987  need_stack_ = true;
988  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
989  isolate_, object, ApplyReplacerFunction(object, key, initial_value),
990  EXCEPTION);
991  }
992 
993  if (IsSmi(*object)) {
994  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
995  return SerializeSmi(Cast<Smi>(*object));
996  }
997 
998  InstanceType instance_type =
999  Cast<HeapObject>(*object)->map(cage_base)->instance_type();
1000  switch (instance_type) {
1001  case HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE:
1002  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
1003  return SerializeHeapNumber(Cast<HeapNumber>(object));
1004  case BIGINT_TYPE:
1005  isolate_->Throw(
1006  *factory()->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kBigIntSerializeJSON));
1007  return EXCEPTION;
1008  case ODDBALL_TYPE:
1009  switch (Cast<Oddball>(*object)->kind()) {
1010  case Oddball::kFalse:
1011  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
1012  AppendCStringLiteral("false");
1013  return SUCCESS;
1014  case Oddball::kTrue:
1015  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
1016  AppendCStringLiteral("true");
1017  return SUCCESS;
1018  case Oddball::kNull:
1019  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
1020  AppendCStringLiteral("null");
1021  return SUCCESS;
1022  default:
1023  return UNCHANGED;
1024  }
1025  case JS_ARRAY_TYPE:
1026  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
1027  return SerializeJSArray(Cast<JSArray>(object), key);
1028  case JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE:
1029  if (!need_stack_) {
1030  need_stack_ = true;
1031  return NEED_STACK;
1032  }
1033  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
1034  return SerializeJSPrimitiveWrapper(Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(object), key);
1035  case SYMBOL_TYPE:
1036  return UNCHANGED;
1037  case JS_RAW_JSON_TYPE:
1038  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
1039  {
1040  DirectHandle<JSRawJson> raw_json_obj = Cast<JSRawJson>(object);
1041  Handle<String> raw_json;
1042  if (raw_json_obj->HasInitialLayout(isolate_)) {
1043  // Fast path: the object returned by JSON.rawJSON has its initial map
1044  // intact.
1045  raw_json = Cast<String>(handle(
1046  raw_json_obj->InObjectPropertyAt(JSRawJson::kRawJsonInitialIndex),
1047  isolate_));
1048  } else {
1049  // Slow path: perform a property get for "rawJSON". Because raw JSON
1050  // objects are created frozen, it is still guaranteed that there will
1051  // be a property named "rawJSON" that is a String. Their initial maps
1052  // only change due to VM-internal operations like being optimized for
1053  // being used as a prototype.
1054  raw_json = Cast<String>(
1055  JSObject::GetProperty(isolate_, raw_json_obj,
1056  isolate_->factory()->raw_json_string())
1057  .ToHandleChecked());
1058  }
1059  AppendString(raw_json);
1060  }
1061  return SUCCESS;
1062  case HOLE_TYPE:
1063  UNREACHABLE();
1064 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1065  case WASM_STRUCT_TYPE:
1066  case WASM_ARRAY_TYPE:
1067  return UNCHANGED;
1068 #endif
1069  default:
1070  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(instance_type)) {
1071  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
1072  SerializeString<false>(Cast<String>(object));
1073  return SUCCESS;
1074  } else {
1075  // Make sure that we have a JSReceiver before we cast it to one.
1076  // If we ever leak an internal object that is not a JSReceiver it could
1077  // end up here and lead to a type confusion.
1078  CHECK(IsJSReceiver(*object));
1079  if (IsCallable(Cast<HeapObject>(*object), cage_base)) return UNCHANGED;
1080  // Go to slow path for global proxy and objects requiring access checks.
1081  if (deferred_string_key) SerializeDeferredKey(comma, key);
1082  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSProxy(instance_type)) {
1083  return SerializeJSProxy(Cast<JSProxy>(object), key);
1084  }
1085  // WASM_{STRUCT,ARRAY}_TYPE are handled in `case:` blocks above.
1086  DCHECK(IsJSObject(*object));
1087  return SerializeJSObject(Cast<JSObject>(object), key);
1088  }
1089  }
1090 
1091  UNREACHABLE();
1092 }
1093 
1094 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeJSPrimitiveWrapper(
1095  Handle<JSPrimitiveWrapper> object, Handle<Object> key) {
1096  Tagged<Object> raw = object->value();
1097  if (IsString(raw)) {
1098  Handle<Object> value;
1099  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1100  isolate_, value, Object::ToString(isolate_, object), EXCEPTION);
1101  SerializeString<false>(Cast<String>(value));
1102  } else if (IsNumber(raw)) {
1103  DirectHandle<Object> value;
1104  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1105  isolate_, value, Object::ToNumber(isolate_, object), EXCEPTION);
1106  if (IsSmi(*value)) return SerializeSmi(Cast<Smi>(*value));
1107  SerializeHeapNumber(Cast<HeapNumber>(value));
1108  } else if (IsBigInt(raw)) {
1109  isolate_->Throw(
1110  *factory()->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kBigIntSerializeJSON));
1111  return EXCEPTION;
1112  } else if (IsBoolean(raw)) {
1113  if (IsTrue(raw, isolate_)) {
1114  AppendCStringLiteral("true");
1115  } else {
1116  AppendCStringLiteral("false");
1117  }
1118  } else {
1119  // ES6 24.3.2.1 step 10.c, serialize as an ordinary JSObject.
1120  return SerializeJSObject(object, key);
1121  }
1122  return SUCCESS;
1123 }

1125 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeSmi(Tagged<Smi> object) {
1126  static_assert(Smi::kMaxValue <= 2147483647);
1127  static_assert(Smi::kMinValue >= -2147483648);
1128  // sizeof(string) includes \0.
1129  static constexpr uint32_t kBufferSize = sizeof("-2147483648") - 1;
1130  char chars[kBufferSize];
1131  base::Vector<char> buffer(chars, kBufferSize);
1132  AppendString(IntToStringView(object.value(), buffer));
1133  return SUCCESS;
1134 }

1136 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeDouble(double number) {
1137  if (std::isinf(number) || std::isnan(number)) {
1138  AppendCStringLiteral("null");
1139  return SUCCESS;
1140  }
1141  static constexpr uint32_t kBufferSize = 100;
1142  char chars[kBufferSize];

1145  AppendString(str);
1146  return SUCCESS;

1148 
1149 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeJSArray(
1150  Handle<JSArray> object, Handle<Object> key) {
1151  uint32_t length = 0;
1152  CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(object->length(), &length));
1153  DCHECK(!IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object));
1154  if (length == 0) {
1155  AppendCStringLiteral("[]");
1156  return SUCCESS;
1157  }
1158 
1159  Result stack_push = StackPush(object, key);
1160  if (stack_push != SUCCESS) return stack_push;
1161 
1162  AppendCharacter('[');
1163  Indent();
1164  uint32_t slow_path_index = 0;
1165  Result result = UNCHANGED;
1166  if (replacer_function_.is_null()) {
1167 #define CASE_WITH_INTERRUPT(kind) \
1168  case kind: \
1169  result = SerializeFixedArrayWithInterruptCheck<kind>(object, length, \
1170  &slow_path_index); \
1171  break;
1172 #define CASE_WITH_TRANSITION(kind) \
1173  case kind: \
1174  result = SerializeFixedArrayWithPossibleTransitions<kind>( \
1175  object, length, &slow_path_index); \
1176  break;
1177 
1178  switch (object->GetElementsKind()) {
1179  CASE_WITH_INTERRUPT(PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS)
1180  CASE_WITH_INTERRUPT(HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS)
1181  CASE_WITH_TRANSITION(PACKED_ELEMENTS)
1182  CASE_WITH_TRANSITION(HOLEY_ELEMENTS)
1183  CASE_WITH_INTERRUPT(PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS)
1184  CASE_WITH_INTERRUPT(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS)
1185  default:
1186  break;
1187  }
1188 
1189 #undef CASE_WITH_TRANSITION
1190 #undef CASE_WITH_INTERRUPT
1191  }
1192  if (result == UNCHANGED) {
1193  // Slow path for non-fast elements and fall-back in edge cases.
1194  result = SerializeArrayLikeSlow(object, slow_path_index, length);
1195  }
1196  if (result != SUCCESS) return result;
1197  Unindent();
1198  NewLine();
1199  AppendCharacter(']');
1200  StackPop();
1201  return SUCCESS;
1202 }
1203 
1204 template <ElementsKind kind>
1205 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeFixedArrayWithInterruptCheck(
1206  DirectHandle<JSArray> array, uint32_t length, uint32_t* slow_path_index) {
1207  static_assert(IsSmiElementsKind(kind) || IsDoubleElementsKind(kind));
1208  using ArrayT = std::conditional_t<IsDoubleElementsKind(kind),
1209  FixedDoubleArray, FixedArray>;
1210 
1211  StackLimitCheck interrupt_check(isolate_);
1212  constexpr uint32_t kInterruptLength = 4000;
1213  uint32_t limit = std::min(length, kInterruptLength);
1214  constexpr uint32_t kMaxAllowedFastPackedLength =
1215  std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() - kInterruptLength;
1216  static_assert(FixedArray::kMaxLength < kMaxAllowedFastPackedLength);
1217 
1218  constexpr bool is_holey = IsHoleyElementsKind(kind);
1219  bool bailout_on_hole =
1220  is_holey ? !CanFastSerializeJSArray(isolate_, *array) : true;
1221 
1222  uint32_t i = 0;
1223  while (true) {
1224  for (; i < limit; i++) {
1225  Result result = SerializeFixedArrayElement<kind>(
1226  Cast<ArrayT>(array->elements()), i, *array, bailout_on_hole);
1227  if constexpr (is_holey) {
1228  if (result != SUCCESS) {
1229  *slow_path_index = i;
1230  return result;
1231  }
1232  } else {
1233  USE(result);
1234  DCHECK_EQ(result, SUCCESS);
1235  }
1236  }
1237  if (i >= length) return SUCCESS;
1238  DCHECK_LT(limit, kMaxAllowedFastPackedLength);
1239  limit = std::min(length, limit + kInterruptLength);
1240  if (interrupt_check.InterruptRequested() &&
1241  IsException(isolate_->stack_guard()->HandleInterrupts(), isolate_)) {
1242  return EXCEPTION;
1243  }
1244  }
1245  return SUCCESS;
1246 }
1247 
1248 template <ElementsKind kind>
1249 JsonStringifier::Result
1250 JsonStringifier::SerializeFixedArrayWithPossibleTransitions(
1251  DirectHandle<JSArray> array, uint32_t length, uint32_t* slow_path_index) {
1252  static_assert(IsObjectElementsKind(kind));
1253 
1254  HandleScope handle_scope(isolate_);
1255  DirectHandle<Object> old_length(array->length(), isolate_);
1256  constexpr bool is_holey = IsHoleyElementsKind(kind);
1257  bool should_check_treat_hole_as_undefined = true;
1258  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
1259  if (array->length() != *old_length || kind != array->GetElementsKind()) {
1260  // Array was modified during SerializeElement.
1261  *slow_path_index = i;
1262  return UNCHANGED;
1263  }
1264  Tagged<Object> current_element =
1265  Cast<FixedArray>(array->elements())->get(i);
1266  if (is_holey && IsTheHole(current_element)) {
1267  if (should_check_treat_hole_as_undefined) {
1268  if (!CanFastSerializeJSArray(isolate_, *array)) {
1269  *slow_path_index = i;
1270  return UNCHANGED;
1271  }
1272  should_check_treat_hole_as_undefined = false;
1273  }
1274  Separator(i == 0);
1275  AppendCStringLiteral("null");
1276  } else {
1277  Separator(i == 0);
1278  Result result = SerializeElement(
1279  isolate_, handle(Cast<JSAny>(current_element), isolate_), i);
1280  if (result == UNCHANGED) {
1281  AppendCStringLiteral("null");
1282  } else if (result != SUCCESS) {
1283  return result;
1284  }
1285  if constexpr (is_holey) {
1286  should_check_treat_hole_as_undefined = true;
1287  }
1288  }
1289  }
1290  return SUCCESS;
1291 }
1292 
1293 template <ElementsKind kind, typename T>
1294 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeFixedArrayElement(
1295  Tagged<T> elements, uint32_t i, Tagged<JSArray> array,
1296  bool bailout_on_hole) {
1297  if constexpr (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
1298  if (elements->is_the_hole(isolate_, i)) {
1299  if (bailout_on_hole) return UNCHANGED;
1300  Separator(i == 0);
1301  AppendCStringLiteral("null");
1302  return SUCCESS;
1303  }
1304  }
1305  DCHECK(!elements->is_the_hole(isolate_, i));
1306  Separator(i == 0);
1307  if constexpr (IsSmiElementsKind(kind)) {
1308  SerializeSmi(Cast<Smi>(elements->get(i)));
1309  } else if constexpr (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
1310  SerializeDouble(elements->get_scalar(i));
1311  } else {
1312  UNREACHABLE();
1313  }
1314  return SUCCESS;
1315 }

1317 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeArrayLikeSlow(
1318  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object, uint32_t start, uint32_t length) {
1319  if (!need_stack_) {
1320  need_stack_ = true;
1321  return NEED_STACK;
1322  }
1323  // We need to write out at least two characters per array element.
1324  static constexpr uint32_t kMaxSerializableArrayLength =
1325  String::kMaxLength / 2;
1326  if (length > kMaxSerializableArrayLength) {
1327  isolate_->Throw(*isolate_->factory()->NewInvalidStringLengthError());
1328  return EXCEPTION;
1329  }
1330  HandleScope handle_scope(isolate_);
1331  for (uint32_t i = start; i < length; i++) {
1332  Separator(i == 0);
1333  Handle<Object> element;
1334  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1335  isolate_, element, JSReceiver::GetElement(isolate_, object, i),
1336  EXCEPTION);
1337  Result result = SerializeElement(isolate_, Cast<JSAny>(element), i);
1338  if (result == SUCCESS) continue;
1339  if (result == UNCHANGED) {
1340  // Detect overflow sooner for large sparse arrays.
1341  if (overflowed_) {
1342  isolate_->Throw(*isolate_->factory()->NewInvalidStringLengthError());
1343  return EXCEPTION;
1344  }
1345  AppendCStringLiteral("null");
1346  } else {
1347  return result;
1348  }
1349  }
1350  return SUCCESS;
1351 }

1353 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeJSObject(
1354  Handle<JSObject> object, Handle<Object> key) {
1355  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate_);
1356  HandleScope handle_scope(isolate_);
1357 
1358  if (!property_list_.is_null() ||
1359  !CanFastSerializeJSObject(*object, isolate_)) {
1360  if (!need_stack_) {
1361  need_stack_ = true;
1362  return NEED_STACK;
1363  }
1364  Result stack_push = StackPush(object, key);
1365  if (stack_push != SUCCESS) return stack_push;
1366  Result result = SerializeJSReceiverSlow(object);
1367  if (result != SUCCESS) return result;
1368  StackPop();
1369  return SUCCESS;
1370  }
1371 
1372  DCHECK(!IsJSGlobalProxy(*object));
1373  DCHECK(!object->HasIndexedInterceptor());
1374  DCHECK(!object->HasNamedInterceptor());
1375 
1376  DirectHandle<Map> map(object->map(cage_base), isolate_);
1377  if (map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() == 0) {
1378  AppendCStringLiteral("{}");
1379  return SUCCESS;
1380  }
1381 
1382  Result stack_push = StackPush(object, key);
1383  if (stack_push != SUCCESS) return stack_push;
1384  AppendCharacter('{');
1385  Indent();
1386  bool comma = false;
1387  for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
1388  Handle<String> key_name;
1389  PropertyDetails details = PropertyDetails::Empty();
1390  {
1391  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1392  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
1393  map->instance_descriptors(cage_base);
1394  Tagged<Name> name = descriptors->GetKey(i);
1395  // TODO(rossberg): Should this throw?
1396  if (!IsString(name, cage_base)) continue;
1397  key_name = handle(Cast<String>(name), isolate_);
1398  details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
1399  }
1400  if (details.IsDontEnum()) continue;
1401  Handle<JSAny> property;
1402  if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField &&
1403  *map == object->map(cage_base)) {
1404  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
1405  FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(*map, details);
1406  if (replacer_function_.is_null()) {
1407  // If there's no replacer function, read the raw property to avoid
1408  // reboxing doubles in mutable boxes.
1409  property = handle(object->RawFastPropertyAt(field_index), isolate_);
1410  } else {
1411  // Rebox the value if there is a replacer function since it could change
1412  // the value in the box.
1413  property = JSObject::FastPropertyAt(
1414  isolate_, object, details.representation(), field_index);
1415  }
1416  } else {
1417  if (!need_stack_) {
1418  need_stack_ = true;
1419  return NEED_STACK;
1420  }
1421  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1422  isolate_, property,
1423  Cast<JSAny>(Object::GetPropertyOrElement(isolate_, object, key_name)),
1424  EXCEPTION);
1425  }
1426  Result result = SerializeProperty(property, comma, key_name);
1427  if (!comma && result == SUCCESS) comma = true;
1428  if (result == EXCEPTION || result == NEED_STACK) return result;
1429  }
1430  Unindent();
1431  if (comma) NewLine();
1432  AppendCharacter('}');
1433  StackPop();
1434  return SUCCESS;
1435 }

1437 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeJSReceiverSlow(
1438  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object) {
1439  DirectHandle<FixedArray> contents = property_list_;
1440  if (contents.is_null()) {
1441  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1442  isolate_, contents,
1443  KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate_, object, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
1444  ENUMERABLE_STRINGS,
1445  GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString),
1446  EXCEPTION);
1447  }
1448  AppendCharacter('{');
1449  Indent();
1450  bool comma = false;
1451  for (int i = 0; i < contents->length(); i++) {
1452  Handle<String> key(Cast<String>(contents->get(i)), isolate_);
1453  Handle<Object> property;
1454  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1455  isolate_, property, Object::GetPropertyOrElement(isolate_, object, key),
1456  EXCEPTION);
1457  Result result = SerializeProperty(Cast<JSAny>(property), comma, key);
1458  if (!comma && result == SUCCESS) comma = true;
1459  if (result == EXCEPTION || result == NEED_STACK) return result;
1460  }
1461  Unindent();
1462  if (comma) NewLine();
1463  AppendCharacter('}');
1464  return SUCCESS;
1465 }

1467 JsonStringifier::Result JsonStringifier::SerializeJSProxy(
1468  Handle<JSProxy> object, Handle<Object> key) {
1469  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
1470  Result stack_push = StackPush(object, key);
1471  if (stack_push != SUCCESS) return stack_push;
1472  Maybe<bool> is_array = Object::IsArray(object);
1473  if (is_array.IsNothing()) return EXCEPTION;
1474  if (is_array.FromJust()) {
1475  DirectHandle<Object> length_object;
1476  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1477  isolate_, length_object,
1478  Object::GetLengthFromArrayLike(isolate_, Cast<JSReceiver>(object)),
1479  EXCEPTION);
1480  uint32_t length;
1481  if (!Object::ToUint32(*length_object, &length)) {
1482  // Technically, we need to be able to handle lengths outside the
1483  // uint32_t range. However, we would run into string size overflow
1484  // if we tried to stringify such an array.
1485  isolate_->Throw(*isolate_->factory()->NewInvalidStringLengthError());
1486  return EXCEPTION;
1487  }
1488  AppendCharacter('[');
1489  Indent();
1490  Result result = SerializeArrayLikeSlow(object, 0, length);
1491  if (result != SUCCESS) return result;
1492  Unindent();
1493  if (length > 0) NewLine();
1494  AppendCharacter(']');
1495  } else {
1496  Result result = SerializeJSReceiverSlow(object);
1497  if (result != SUCCESS) return result;
1498  }
1499  StackPop();
1500  return SUCCESS;
1501 }

1503 template <typename SrcChar, typename DestChar, bool raw_json>
1504 bool JsonStringifier::SerializeStringUnchecked_(
1505  base::Vector<const SrcChar> src, NoExtendBuilder<DestChar>* dest) {
1506  // Assert that base::uc16 character is not truncated down to 8 bit.
1507  // The <base::uc16, char> version of this method must not be called.
1508  DCHECK(sizeof(DestChar) >= sizeof(SrcChar));
1509  bool required_escaping = false;
1510  size_t uncopied_src_index = 0; // Index of first char not copied yet.
1511  for (size_t i = 0; i < src.size(); i++) {
1512  SrcChar c = src[i];
1513  if (raw_json || DoNotEscape(c)) {
1514  continue;
1515  } else if (sizeof(SrcChar) != 1 &&
1516  base::IsInRange(c, static_cast<SrcChar>(0xD800),
1517  static_cast<SrcChar>(0xDFFF))) {
1518  // The current character is a surrogate.
1519  required_escaping = true;
1520  dest->AppendSubstring(src.data(), uncopied_src_index, i);
1521 
1522  char double_to_radix_chars[kDoubleToRadixMaxChars];
1523  base::Vector<char> double_to_radix_buffer =
1524  base::ArrayVector(double_to_radix_chars);
1525  if (c <= 0xDBFF) {
1526  // The current character is a leading surrogate.
1527  if (i + 1 < src.size()) {
1528  // There is a next character.
1529  SrcChar next = src[i + 1];
1530  if (base::IsInRange(next, static_cast<SrcChar>(0xDC00),
1531  static_cast<SrcChar>(0xDFFF))) {
1532  // The next character is a trailing surrogate, meaning this is a
1533  // surrogate pair.
1534  dest->Append(c);
1535  dest->Append(next);
1536  i++;
1537  } else {
1538  // The next character is not a trailing surrogate. Thus, the
1539  // current character is a lone leading surrogate.
1540  dest->AppendCString("\\u");
1541  std::string_view hex =
1542  DoubleToRadixStringView(c, 16, double_to_radix_buffer);
1543  dest->AppendString(hex);
1544  }
1545  } else {
1546  // There is no next character. Thus, the current character is a lone
1547  // leading surrogate.
1548  dest->AppendCString("\\u");
1549  std::string_view hex =
1550  DoubleToRadixStringView(c, 16, double_to_radix_buffer);
1551  dest->AppendString(hex);
1552  }
1553  } else {
1554  // The current character is a lone trailing surrogate. (If it had been
1555  // preceded by a leading surrogate, we would've ended up in the other
1556  // branch earlier on, and the current character would've been handled
1557  // as part of the surrogate pair already.)
1558  dest->AppendCString("\\u");
1559  std::string_view hex =
1560  DoubleToRadixStringView(c, 16, double_to_radix_buffer);
1561  dest->AppendString(hex);
1562  }
1563  uncopied_src_index = i + 1;
1564  } else {
1565  required_escaping = true;
1566  dest->AppendSubstring(src.data(), uncopied_src_index, i);
1567  DCHECK_LT(c, 0x60);
1568  dest->AppendCString(&JsonEscapeTable[c * kJsonEscapeTableEntrySize]);
1569  uncopied_src_index = i + 1;
1570  }
1571  }
1572  dest->AppendSubstring(src.data(), uncopied_src_index, src.size());
1573  return required_escaping;
1574 }

1576 template <typename SrcChar, typename DestChar, bool raw_json>
1577 bool JsonStringifier::SerializeString_(Tagged<String> string,
1578  const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
1579  bool required_escaping = false;
1580  if (!raw_json) Append<uint8_t, DestChar>('"');
1581  // We might be able to fit the whole escaped string in the current string
1582  // part, or we might need to allocate.
1583  base::Vector<const SrcChar> vector = string->GetCharVector<SrcChar>(no_gc);
1584  if V8_LIKELY (EscapedLengthIfCurrentPartFits(vector.size())) {
1585  NoExtendBuilder<DestChar> no_extend(
1586  reinterpret_cast<DestChar*>(part_ptr_) + current_index_,
1587  &current_index_);
1588  required_escaping = SerializeStringUnchecked_<SrcChar, DestChar, raw_json>(
1589  vector, &no_extend);
1590  } else {
1591  DCHECK(encoding_ == String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING ||
1592  (string->IsFlat() &&
1593  String::IsOneByteRepresentationUnderneath(string)));
1594  size_t uncopied_src_index = 0; // Index of first char not copied yet.
1595  for (size_t i = 0; i < vector.size(); i++) {
1596  SrcChar c = vector.at(i);
1597  if (raw_json || DoNotEscape(c)) {
1598  continue;
1599  } else if (sizeof(SrcChar) != 1 &&
1600  base::IsInRange(c, static_cast<SrcChar>(0xD800),
1601  static_cast<SrcChar>(0xDFFF))) {
1602  // The current character is a surrogate.
1603  required_escaping = true;
1604  AppendSubstring(vector.data(), uncopied_src_index, i);
1605 
1606  char double_to_radix_chars[kDoubleToRadixMaxChars];
1607  base::Vector<char> double_to_radix_buffer =
1608  base::ArrayVector(double_to_radix_chars);
1609  if (c <= 0xDBFF) {
1610  // The current character is a leading surrogate.
1611  if (i + 1 < vector.size()) {
1612  // There is a next character.
1613  SrcChar next = vector.at(i + 1);
1614  if (base::IsInRange(next, static_cast<SrcChar>(0xDC00),
1615  static_cast<SrcChar>(0xDFFF))) {
1616  // The next character is a trailing surrogate, meaning this is a
1617  // surrogate pair.
1618  Append<SrcChar, DestChar>(c);
1619  Append<SrcChar, DestChar>(next);
1620  i++;
1621  } else {
1622  // The next character is not a trailing surrogate. Thus, the
1623  // current character is a lone leading surrogate.
1624  AppendCStringLiteral("\\u");
1625  std::string_view hex =
1626  DoubleToRadixStringView(c, 16, double_to_radix_buffer);
1627  AppendString(hex);
1628  }
1629  } else {
1630  // There is no next character. Thus, the current character is a
1631  // lone leading surrogate.
1632  AppendCStringLiteral("\\u");
1633  std::string_view hex =
1634  DoubleToRadixStringView(c, 16, double_to_radix_buffer);
1635  AppendString(hex);
1636  }
1637  } else {
1638  // The current character is a lone trailing surrogate. (If it had
1639  // been preceded by a leading surrogate, we would've ended up in the
1640  // other branch earlier on, and the current character would've been
1641  // handled as part of the surrogate pair already.)
1642  AppendCStringLiteral("\\u");
1643  std::string_view hex =
1644  DoubleToRadixStringView(c, 16, double_to_radix_buffer);
1645  AppendString(hex);
1646  }
1647  uncopied_src_index = i + 1;
1648  } else {
1649  required_escaping = true;
1650  AppendSubstring(vector.data(), uncopied_src_index, i);
1651  DCHECK_LT(c, 0x60);
1652  AppendCString(&JsonEscapeTable[c * kJsonEscapeTableEntrySize]);
1653  uncopied_src_index = i + 1;
1654  }
1655  }
1656  AppendSubstring(vector.data(), uncopied_src_index, vector.size());
1657  }
1658  if (!raw_json) Append<uint8_t, DestChar>('"');
1659  return required_escaping;
1660 }

1662 template <typename DestChar>
1663 bool JsonStringifier::TrySerializeSimplePropertyKey(
1664  Tagged<String> key, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
1665  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate_);
1666  if (key->map() != roots.internalized_one_byte_string_map()) {
1667  return false;
1668  }
1669  if (!key_cache_.Contains(key)) {
1670  return false;
1671  }
1672  size_t length = key->length();
1673  size_t copy_length = length;
1674  if constexpr (sizeof(DestChar) == 1) {
1675  // CopyChars has fast paths for small integer lengths, and is generally a
1676  // little faster if we round the length up to the nearest 4. This is still
1677  // within the bounds of the object on the heap, because object alignment is
1678  // never less than 4 for any build configuration.
1679  constexpr int kRounding = 4;
1680  static_assert(kRounding <= kObjectAlignment);
1681  copy_length = RoundUp(length, kRounding);
1682  }
1683  // Add three for the quote marks and colon, to determine how much output space
1684  // is needed. We might actually require a little less output space than this,
1685  // depending on how much rounding happened above, but it's more important to
1686  // compute the requirement quickly than to be precise.
1687  size_t required_length = copy_length + 3;
1688  if (!CurrentPartCanFit(required_length)) {
1689  return false;
1690  }
1691  NoExtendBuilder<DestChar> no_extend(
1692  reinterpret_cast<DestChar*>(part_ptr_) + current_index_, &current_index_);
1693  no_extend.Append('"');
1694  base::Vector<const uint8_t> chars(
1695  Cast<SeqOneByteString>(key)->GetChars(no_gc), copy_length);
1696  DCHECK_LE(reinterpret_cast<Address>(chars.end()),
1697  key.address() + key->Size());
1698 #if DEBUG
1699  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
1700  DCHECK(DoNotEscape(chars[i]));
1701  }
1702 #endif // DEBUG
1703  no_extend.AppendChars(chars, length);
1704  no_extend.Append('"');
1705  no_extend.Append(':');
1706  return true;
1707 }

1724 void JsonStringifier::SerializeDeferredKey(bool deferred_comma,
1725  Handle<Object> deferred_key) {
1726  Separator(!deferred_comma);
1727  Handle<String> string_key = Cast<String>(deferred_key);
1728  bool wrote_simple = false;
1729  {
1730  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1731  wrote_simple =
1732  encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING
1733  ? TrySerializeSimplePropertyKey<uint8_t>(*string_key, no_gc)
1734  : TrySerializeSimplePropertyKey<base::uc16>(*string_key, no_gc);
1735  }
1736 
1737  if (!wrote_simple) {
1738  bool required_escaping = SerializeString<false>(string_key);
1739  if (!required_escaping) {
1740  key_cache_.TryInsert(*string_key);
1741  }
1742  AppendCharacter(':');
1743  }
1744 
1745  if (gap_ != nullptr) AppendCharacter(' ');
1746 }

1748 template <bool raw_json>
1749 bool JsonStringifier::SerializeString(Handle<String> object) {
1750  object = String::Flatten(isolate_, object);
1751  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1752  auto string = *object;
1753  if (encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING) {
1754  if (String::IsOneByteRepresentationUnderneath(string)) {
1755  return SerializeString_<uint8_t, uint8_t, raw_json>(string, no_gc);
1756  } else {
1757  ChangeEncoding();
1758  }
1759  }
1760  DCHECK_EQ(encoding_, String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING);
1761  if (String::IsOneByteRepresentationUnderneath(string)) {
1762  return SerializeString_<uint8_t, base::uc16, raw_json>(string, no_gc);
1763  } else {
1764  return SerializeString_<base::uc16, base::uc16, raw_json>(string, no_gc);
1765  }
1766 }
1767 
1768 void JsonStringifier::Extend() {
1769  if (part_length_ >= String::kMaxLength) {
1770  // Set the flag and carry on. Delay throwing the exception till the end.
1771  current_index_ = 0;
1772  overflowed_ = true;
1773  return;
1774  }
1775  part_length_ *= kPartLengthGrowthFactor;
1776  if (encoding_ == String::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING) {
1777  uint8_t* tmp_ptr = new uint8_t[part_length_];
1778  memcpy(tmp_ptr, one_byte_ptr_, current_index_);
1779  if (one_byte_ptr_ != one_byte_array_) delete[] one_byte_ptr_;
1780  one_byte_ptr_ = tmp_ptr;
1781  part_ptr_ = one_byte_ptr_;
1782  } else {
1783  base::uc16* tmp_ptr = new base::uc16[part_length_];
1784  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < current_index_; i++) {
1785  tmp_ptr[i] = two_byte_ptr_[i];
1786  }
1787  delete[] two_byte_ptr_;
1788  two_byte_ptr_ = tmp_ptr;
1789  part_ptr_ = two_byte_ptr_;
1790  }
1791 }
1792 
1793 void JsonStringifier::ChangeEncoding() {
1794  encoding_ = String::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
1795  two_byte_ptr_ = new base::uc16[part_length_];
1796  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < current_index_; i++) {
1797  two_byte_ptr_[i] = one_byte_ptr_[i];
1798  }
1799  part_ptr_ = two_byte_ptr_;
1800  if (one_byte_ptr_ != one_byte_array_) delete[] one_byte_ptr_;
1801  one_byte_ptr_ = nullptr;
1802 }

1804 template <typename Char>
1805 class OutBuffer {
1806  public:
1807  explicit OutBuffer(AccountingAllocator* allocator) : allocator_(allocator) {
1808  cur_ = stack_buffer_;
1809  segment_end_ = cur_ + kStackBufferSize;
1810  }
1811  template <typename SrcChar>
1812  requires(sizeof(Char) >= sizeof(SrcChar))
1813  V8_INLINE void AppendCharacter(SrcChar c) {
1814  ReduceCurrentCapacity(1);
1815  DCHECK_GE(SegmentFreeChars(), 1);
1816  *cur_++ = c;
1817  }
1818  template <typename SrcChar>
1819  requires(sizeof(Char) >= sizeof(SrcChar))
1820  void Append(const SrcChar* chars, size_t length) {
1821  ReduceCurrentCapacity(length);
1822  DCHECK_GE(SegmentFreeChars(), length);
1823  CopyChars(cur_, chars, length);
1824  cur_ += length;
1825  }
1826  void EnsureCapacity(size_t size) {
1827 #ifdef DEBUG
1828  current_requested_capacity_ = size;
1829 #endif
1830  if (V8_LIKELY(size <= SegmentFreeChars())) return;
1831  Extend(size);
1832  DCHECK_GE(CurSegmentCapacity(), size);
1833  }
1834  size_t length() const {
1835  if (ZoneUsed()) {
1836  DCHECK_GT(segments_->length(), 0);
1837  size_t length = stack_buffer_size_;
1838  for (int i = 0; i < segments_->length() - 1; i++) {
1839  length += segments_->at(i).size();
1840  }
1841  length += CurSegmentLength();
1842  return length;
1843  } else {
1844  return StackBufferLength();
1845  }
1846  }
1847  template <typename Dst>
1848  void CopyTo(Dst* dst) {
1849  if (ZoneUsed()) {
1850  // Copy stack segment.
1851  CopyChars(dst, stack_buffer_, stack_buffer_size_);
1852  dst += stack_buffer_size_;
1853  // Copy full segments.
1854  DCHECK_GT(segments_->length(), 0);
1855  for (int i = 0; i < segments_->length() - 1; i++) {
1856  base::Vector<Char> segment = segments_.value()[i];
1857  size_t segment_length = segment.size();
1858  CopyChars(dst, segment.begin(), segment_length);
1859  dst += segment_length;
1860  }
1861  // Copy last (partially filled) segment.
1862  base::Vector<Char> segment = segments_->last();
1863  CopyChars(dst, segment.begin(), CurSegmentLength());
1864  } else {
1865  // Copy (partially filled) stack segment.
1866  CopyChars(dst, stack_buffer_, StackBufferLength());
1867  }
1868  }
1869 
1870  private:
1871  static constexpr uint32_t kInitialSegmentSize = 2 * KB;
1872  static constexpr uint32_t kMaxSegmentSize = 32 * KB;
1873  static_assert(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(kInitialSegmentSize));
1874  static_assert(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(kMaxSegmentSize));
1875  static constexpr uint8_t kInitialSegmentSizeHighestBit =
1876  kBitsPerInt - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(kInitialSegmentSize) - 1;
1877  static constexpr uint8_t kMaxSegmentSizeHighestBit =
1878  kBitsPerInt - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(kMaxSegmentSize) - 1;
1879  static constexpr uint8_t kNumVariableSegments =
1880  kMaxSegmentSizeHighestBit - kInitialSegmentSizeHighestBit;
1881  static constexpr size_t kStackBufferSize = 256;
1882 
1883  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void Extend(size_t min_size) {
1884  if (ZoneUsed()) {
1885  segments_->last().Truncate(CurSegmentLength());
1886  } else {
1887  stack_buffer_size_ = StackBufferLength();
1888  zone_.emplace(allocator_, kJsonStringifierZoneName);
1889  segments_.emplace(1, &zone_.value());
1890  }
1891  const size_t new_segment_size =
1892  std::max(min_size, SegmentCapacity(segments_->length()));
1893  segments_->Add(zone_->AllocateVector<Char>(new_segment_size),
1894  &zone_.value());
1895  cur_ = segments_->last().begin();
1896  segment_end_ = segments_->last().end();
1897  }
1898  V8_INLINE size_t SegmentFreeChars() const { return segment_end_ - cur_; }
1899  V8_INLINE size_t StackBufferLength() const {
1900  DCHECK(!ZoneUsed());
1901  return cur_ - stack_buffer_;
1902  }
1903  V8_INLINE size_t CurSegmentLength() const {
1904  DCHECK(ZoneUsed());
1905  return cur_ - segments_->last().begin();
1906  }
1907  V8_INLINE size_t SegmentCapacity(size_t segment) {
1908  return 1u << std::min<size_t>(segment + kInitialSegmentSizeHighestBit,
1909  kMaxSegmentSizeHighestBit);
1910  }
1911  V8_INLINE size_t CurSegmentCapacity() {
1912  DCHECK(ZoneUsed());
1913  DCHECK_GT(segments_->length(), 0);
1914  return segments_->last().size();
1915  }
1916  V8_INLINE void ReduceCurrentCapacity(size_t size) {
1917 #ifdef DEBUG
1918  DCHECK_LE(size, current_requested_capacity_);
1919  current_requested_capacity_ -= size;
1920 #endif
1921  }
1922  V8_INLINE bool ZoneUsed() const { return zone_.has_value(); }
1923 
1924  AccountingAllocator* allocator_;
1925  Char stack_buffer_[kStackBufferSize];
1926  size_t stack_buffer_size_;
1927  Char* cur_;
1928  Char* segment_end_;
1929  std::optional<Zone> zone_;
1930  std::optional<ZoneList<base::Vector<Char>>> segments_;
1931 #ifdef DEBUG
1932  size_t current_requested_capacity_;
1933 #endif
1934 };

2322  Tagged<HeapObject> initial_proto,
2323  Isolate* isolate) {
2324  // Check if the prototype is the initial array prototype without interesting
2325  // properties (toJSON).
2326  Tagged<Map> map = object->map();
2327  if (V8_UNLIKELY(map->may_have_interesting_properties())) return false;
2328  Tagged<HeapObject> proto = map->prototype();
2329  // Note: This will also fail for sub-objects in different native contexts.
2330  // This should be rare and bailing-out to the slow-path is fine.
2331  return V8_LIKELY(proto == initial_proto);
2332 }
2333 
2334 V8_INLINE bool CanFastSerializeJSObjectFastPath(
2335  Tagged<JSObject> object, Tagged<HeapObject> initial_proto, Tagged<Map> map,
2336  Isolate* isolate) {
2337  if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(map))) return false;
2338  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!object->HasFastProperties())) return false;
2339  auto roots = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate);
2340  auto elements = object->elements();
2341  if (V8_UNLIKELY(elements != roots.empty_fixed_array() &&
2342  elements != roots.empty_slow_element_dictionary())) {
2343  return false;
2344  }
2345  if (V8_UNLIKELY(map->may_have_interesting_properties())) return false;
2346  Tagged<HeapObject> proto = map->prototype();
2347  // Note: This will also fail for sub-objects in different native contexts.
2348  // This should be rare and bailing-out to the slow-path is fine.
2349  return V8_LIKELY(proto == initial_proto);
2350 }

2386 FastJsonStringifier<Char>::SerializeObjectKey(
2387  Tagged<String> key, bool comma, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
2388 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL

2390  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate_);

2396  } else if (map == roots.external_internalized_one_byte_string_map() ||
2397  map ==
2398  roots.uncached_external_internalized_one_byte_string_map()) {

2409  return FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult::kChangeEncoding;
2410  }
2411  } else {

2413  return SerializeObjectKey<SeqTwoByteString, no_escaping>(key, comma,

2420  }

2451 // The worst case length of an escaped character is 6. Shifting the string
2452 // length left by 3 is a more pessimistic estimate, but faster to calculate.
2453 size_t MaxEscapedStringLength(size_t length) { return length << 3; }
2454 
2455 } // namespace
2456 
2457 template <typename Char>
2458 template <typename StringT, bool no_escaping>
2459 FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult
2460 FastJsonStringifier<Char>::SerializeObjectKey(
2461  Tagged<String> obj, bool comma, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
2462  using StringChar = StringT::Char;
2463  if constexpr (is_one_byte && sizeof(StringChar) == 2) {
2464  // no_escaping is only possible if we have already seen all the keys in a
2465  // map. But it is not possible we have seen a two-byte string and are still
2466  // in one-byte mode.
2467  if constexpr (no_escaping) {
2468  UNREACHABLE();
2469  } else {
2470  return FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult::kChangeEncoding;
2471  }
2472  } else {
2473  Tagged<StringT> string = Cast<StringT>(obj);
2474  const StringChar* chars;
2475  if constexpr (requires { string->GetChars(no_gc); }) {
2476  chars = string->GetChars(no_gc);
2477  } else {
2478  chars = string->GetChars();
2479  }
2480  const uint32_t length = string->length();
2481  size_t max_length;
2482  if constexpr (no_escaping) {
2483  max_length = length;
2484  } else {
2485  max_length = MaxEscapedStringLength(length);
2486  }
2487  max_length += 4 /* optional comma + 2x double quote + colon */;
2488  EnsureCapacity(max_length);
2489  SeparatorUnchecked(comma);
2490  AppendCharacterUnchecked('"');
2491  FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult result;
2492  if constexpr (no_escaping) {
2493  DCHECK(IsFastKey(obj, no_gc));
2494  SLOW_DCHECK(String::DoesNotContainEscapeCharacters(obj));
2495  AppendStringNoEscapes(chars, length, no_gc);
2496  result = FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult::kSuccess;
2497  } else {
2498  bool needs_escaping = AppendString(chars, length, no_gc);
2499  DCHECK_IMPLIES(needs_escaping, !IsFastKey(obj, no_gc));
2500  SLOW_DCHECK(needs_escaping !=
2501  String::DoesNotContainEscapeCharacters(obj));
2502  result = sizeof(StringChar) == 1 && !needs_escaping
2503  ? FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult::kSuccess
2504  : FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult::kSlow;
2505  }
2506  AppendCharacterUnchecked('"');
2507  AppendCharacterUnchecked(':');
2508  return result;
2509  }
2510 }

2512 template <typename Char>
2513 template <typename StringT>
2514 FastJsonStringifierResult FastJsonStringifier<Char>::SerializeString(
2515  Tagged<HeapObject> obj, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
2516  using StringChar = StringT::Char;
2517  if constexpr (is_one_byte && sizeof(StringChar) == 2) {
2518  return CHANGE_ENCODING;
2519  } else {
2520  Tagged<StringT> string = Cast<StringT>(obj);
2521  const StringChar* chars;
2522  if constexpr (requires { string->GetChars(no_gc); }) {
2523  chars = string->GetChars(no_gc);
2524  } else {
2525  chars = string->GetChars();
2526  }
2527  const uint32_t length = string->length();
2528  EnsureCapacity(MaxEscapedStringLength(length) + 2 /* 2x double quote */);
2529  AppendCharacterUnchecked('"');
2530  AppendString(chars, length, no_gc);
2531  AppendCharacterUnchecked('"');
2532  return SUCCESS;
2533  }

2536 template <typename Char>
2537 FastJsonStringifierResult FastJsonStringifier<Char>::TrySerializeSimpleObject(
2538  Tagged<JSAny> object) {
2539  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2540  // GCMole doesn't handle kNoGC interrupts correctly.
2541  DisableGCMole no_gc_mole;
2542 
2543  if (IsSmi(object)) {
2544  SerializeSmi(Cast<Smi>(object));
2545  return SUCCESS;
2546  }
2547  Tagged<HeapObject> obj = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
2548  Tagged<Map> map = obj->map();
2549  InstanceType instance_type = map->instance_type();
2550  switch (instance_type) {
2551  case INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2552  case SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2553  return SerializeString<SeqOneByteString>(obj, no_gc);
2554  case EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2555  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2556  case EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2557  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2558  return SerializeString<ExternalOneByteString>(obj, no_gc);
2559  case THIN_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE: {
2560  Tagged<String> actual = Cast<ThinString>(obj)->actual();
2561  if (IsExternalString(actual)) {
2562  return SerializeString<ExternalOneByteString>(actual, no_gc);
2563  } else {
2564  return SerializeString<SeqOneByteString>(actual, no_gc);
2565  }
2566  }
2567  case INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2568  case SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2569  return SerializeString<SeqTwoByteString>(obj, no_gc);
2570  case EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2571  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2572  case EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2573  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2574  return SerializeString<ExternalTwoByteString>(obj, no_gc);
2575  case THIN_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE: {
2576  if constexpr (is_one_byte) {
2577  return CHANGE_ENCODING;
2578  } else {
2579  Tagged<String> actual = Cast<ThinString>(obj)->actual();
2580  if (IsExternalString(actual)) {
2581  return SerializeString<ExternalTwoByteString>(actual, no_gc);
2582  } else {
2583  return SerializeString<SeqTwoByteString>(actual, no_gc);
2584  }
2585  }
2586  }
2587  case HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE:
2588  SerializeDouble(Cast<HeapNumber>(obj)->value());
2589  return SUCCESS;
2590  case ODDBALL_TYPE:
2591  switch (Cast<Oddball>(obj)->kind()) {
2592  case Oddball::kFalse:
2593  AppendCStringLiteral("false");
2594  return SUCCESS;
2595  case Oddball::kTrue:
2596  AppendCStringLiteral("true");
2597  return SUCCESS;
2598  case Oddball::kNull:
2599  AppendCStringLiteral("null");
2600  return SUCCESS;
2601  default:
2602  return UNDEFINED;
2603  }
2604  case SYMBOL_TYPE:
2605  return UNDEFINED;
2606  case JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE:
2607  return SerializeJSPrimitiveWrapper(Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(obj), no_gc);
2608  case JS_OBJECT_TYPE:
2609  return JS_OBJECT;
2610  case JS_ARRAY_TYPE:
2611  return JS_ARRAY;
2612  default:
2613  return SLOW_PATH;
2614  }
2615 
2616  UNREACHABLE();
2617 }

2621 Builtin GetBuiltin(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> obj,
2622  DirectHandle<Name> name) {
2623  HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2624 
2625  DirectHandle<JSObject> obj_handle = direct_handle(obj, isolate);
2626  LookupIterator it(isolate, obj_handle, name, obj_handle);
2627  if (!it.IsFound()) {
2628  return Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
2629  }
2630  if (it.state() != LookupIterator::DATA) {
2631  return Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
2632  }
2633  DirectHandle<Object> fun = Object::GetProperty(&it).ToHandleChecked();
2634  if (!IsJSFunction(*fun)) {
2635  return Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
2636  }
2637  return Cast<JSFunction>(*fun)->code(isolate)->builtin_id();
2638 }

2642 template <typename Char>
2643 FastJsonStringifierResult
2644 FastJsonStringifier<Char>::SerializeJSPrimitiveWrapper(
2645  Tagged<JSPrimitiveWrapper> obj, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
2646  // TODO(pthier): Consider extending IsStringWrapperToPrimitive to also cover
2647  // toString() and all JSPrimitiveWrappers to avoid some of the checks here.
2648  if (V8_UNLIKELY(MayHaveInterestingProperties(isolate_, obj))) {
2649  return SLOW_PATH;
2650  }
2651 
2652  Tagged<JSAny> raw = obj->value();
2653  if (IsSymbol(raw)) {
2654  // Symbol object wrapper is treated as a regular object.
2655  Tagged<Map> map = obj->map();
2656  // Check that object has no own properties.
2657  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!obj->HasFastProperties())) return SLOW_PATH;
2658  if (V8_UNLIKELY(map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() != 0)) return SLOW_PATH;
2659  // Check that object has no elements.
2660  auto roots = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate_);
2661  auto elements = obj->elements();
2662  if (V8_UNLIKELY(elements != roots.empty_fixed_array() &&
2663  elements != roots.empty_slow_element_dictionary())) {
2664  return SLOW_PATH;
2665  }
2666 
2667  AppendCStringLiteral("{}");
2668  return SUCCESS;
2669  } else if (IsString(raw)) {
2670  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Protectors::IsStringWrapperToPrimitiveIntact(isolate_))) {
2671  return SLOW_PATH;
2672  }
2673  // We only fetch data properties in GetBuiltin, but GCMole doesn't know
2674  // that and assumes GCs can happen.
2675  DisableGCMole no_gc_mole;
2676  // Check that toString() on the prototype chain is the expected builtin.
2677  if (V8_UNLIKELY(
2678  GetBuiltin(isolate_, obj, isolate_->factory()->toString_string()) !=
2679  Builtin::kStringPrototypeToString)) {
2680  return SLOW_PATH;
2681  }
2682 
2683  Tagged<String> string = Cast<String>(raw);
2684  while (true) {
2685  FastJsonStringifierResult result =
2686  string->DispatchToSpecificType(absl::Overload{
2687  [&](Tagged<SeqOneByteString> str) {
2688  return SerializeString<SeqOneByteString>(str, no_gc);
2689  },
2690  [&](Tagged<SeqTwoByteString> str) {
2691  return SerializeString<SeqTwoByteString>(str, no_gc);
2692  },
2693  [&](Tagged<ExternalOneByteString> str) {
2694  return SerializeString<ExternalOneByteString>(str, no_gc);
2695  },
2696  [&](Tagged<ExternalTwoByteString> str) {
2697  return SerializeString<ExternalTwoByteString>(str, no_gc);
2698  },
2699  [&](Tagged<ThinString> str) {
2700  string = str->actual();
2701  // UNDEFINED is misused here to indicate that we continue after
2702  // unwrapping.
2703  return UNDEFINED;
2704  },
2705  [&](Tagged<ConsString> str) { return SLOW_PATH; },
2706  [&](Tagged<SlicedString> str) { return SLOW_PATH; }});
2707  if (V8_LIKELY(result != UNDEFINED)) return result;
2708  }
2709  UNREACHABLE();
2710  } else if (IsNumber(raw)) {
2711  // We only fetch data properties in GetBuiltin, but GCMole doesn't know
2712  // that and assumes GCs can happen.
2713  DisableGCMole no_gc_mole;
2714  // Check that valueOf() on the prototype chain is the expected builtin.
2715  if (V8_UNLIKELY(
2716  GetBuiltin(isolate_, obj, isolate_->factory()->valueOf_string()) !=
2717  Builtin::kNumberPrototypeValueOf)) {
2718  return SLOW_PATH;
2719  }
2720  if (IsSmi(raw)) {
2721  SerializeSmi(Cast<Smi>(raw));
2722  return SUCCESS;
2723  }
2724  DCHECK(IsHeapNumber(raw));
2725  SerializeDouble(Cast<HeapNumber>(raw)->value());
2726  return SUCCESS;
2727  } else if (IsBoolean(raw)) {
2728  if (IsTrue(raw, isolate_)) {
2729  AppendCStringLiteral("true");
2730  } else {
2731  AppendCStringLiteral("false");
2732  }
2733  return SUCCESS;
2734  } else if (IsBigInt(raw)) {
2735  return SLOW_PATH;
2736  }
2737 
2738  UNREACHABLE();
2739 }

2741 template <typename Char>
2742 FastJsonStringifierResult FastJsonStringifier<Char>::SerializeJSObject(
2743  Tagged<JSObject> obj, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
2744  Tagged<Map> map = obj->map();
2745  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!CanFastSerializeJSObjectFastPath(
2746  obj, initial_jsobject_proto_, map, isolate_))) {
2747  return SLOW_PATH;
2748  }
2749  AppendCharacter('{');
2750  const uint16_t nof_descriptors = map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
2751  const uint8_t in_object_properties = map->GetInObjectProperties();
2752  const uint8_t in_object_properties_start =
2753  map->GetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords();
2754  const Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = map->instance_descriptors();
2755  FastIterableState fast_iterable_state = descriptors->fast_iterable();
2756  switch (fast_iterable_state) {
2757 #define CASE(state) \
2758  case FastIterableState::state: \
2759  return ResumeJSObject<FastIterableState::state>( \
2760  obj, 0, nof_descriptors, in_object_properties, \
2761  in_object_properties_start, descriptors, false, no_gc)
2762  CASE(kUnknown);
2763  CASE(kJsonFast);
2764  CASE(kJsonSlow);
2765 #undef CASE
2766  }
2767  UNREACHABLE();
2768 }

2770 template <typename Char>
2771 template <DescriptorArray::FastIterableState fast_iterable_state>
2772 FastJsonStringifierResult FastJsonStringifier<Char>::ResumeJSObject(
2773  Tagged<JSObject> obj, uint16_t start_descriptor_idx,
2774  uint16_t nof_descriptors, uint8_t in_object_properties,
2775  uint8_t in_object_properties_start, Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors,
2776  bool comma, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
2777  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase();
2778  InternalIndex::Range range{start_descriptor_idx, nof_descriptors};
2779  for (InternalIndex i : range) {
2780  // We don't deal with dictionary mode objects on the fast-path, so the index
2781  // is guaranteed to be less than uint16_t::max.
2782  static_assert(kMaxNumberOfDescriptors <
2783  std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max());
2784  DCHECK_LE(i.as_uint32(), kMaxNumberOfDescriptors);
2785  const uint16_t descriptor_idx = static_cast<uint16_t>(i.as_uint32());
2786 
2787  Tagged<Name> name = descriptors->GetKey(i);
2788  int property_index;
2789  if constexpr (fast_iterable_state != FastIterableState::kJsonFast) {
2790  if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsSymbol(name))) {
2791  if constexpr (fast_iterable_state == FastIterableState::kUnknown) {
2792  descriptors->set_fast_iterable(FastIterableState::kJsonSlow);
2793  }
2794  continue;
2795  }
2796  PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
2797  if (V8_UNLIKELY(details.IsDontEnum())) {
2798  if constexpr (fast_iterable_state == FastIterableState::kUnknown) {
2799  descriptors->set_fast_iterable(FastIterableState::kJsonSlow);
2800  }
2801  continue;
2802  }
2803  if (V8_UNLIKELY(details.location() != PropertyLocation::kField)) {
2804  descriptors->set_fast_iterable(FastIterableState::kJsonSlow);
2805  return SLOW_PATH;
2806  }
2807  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
2808  property_index = details.field_index();
2809  } else {
2810  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor_idx, descriptors->GetDetails(i).field_index());
2811  property_index = descriptor_idx;
2812  }
2813  const bool is_inobject = property_index < in_object_properties;
2814  Tagged<JSAny> property;
2815  if (is_inobject) {
2816  int offset = (in_object_properties_start + property_index) * kTaggedSize;
2817  property = TaggedField<JSAny>::Relaxed_Load(cage_base, obj, offset);
2818  } else {
2819  property_index -= in_object_properties;
2820  property = obj->property_array(cage_base)->get(cage_base, property_index);
2821  }
2822 
2823  DCHECK(IsInternalizedString(name));
2824  Tagged<String> key_name = Cast<String>(name);
2825 
2826  if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsUndefined(property) || IsSymbol(property))) {
2827  if constexpr (fast_iterable_state == FastIterableState::kUnknown) {
2828  // Even if we don't serialize the key, check if it is fast iterable to
2829  // avoid false positives in DescriptorArray::fast_iterable.
2830  if (!IsFastKey(key_name, no_gc)) {
2831  descriptors->set_fast_iterable(FastIterableState::kJsonSlow);
2832  }
2833  }
2834  continue;
2835  }
2836 
2837  FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult key_result;
2838  if constexpr (fast_iterable_state == FastIterableState::kJsonFast) {
2839  V8_INLINE_STATEMENT key_result =
2840  SerializeObjectKey<true>(key_name, comma, no_gc);
2841  DCHECK_EQ(key_result, FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult::kSuccess);
2842  } else {
2843  key_result = SerializeObjectKey<false>(key_name, comma, no_gc);
2844  if (V8_UNLIKELY(key_result !=
2845  FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult::kSuccess)) {
2846  descriptors->set_fast_iterable(FastIterableState::kJsonSlow);
2847  if constexpr (is_one_byte) {
2848  if (key_result ==
2849  FastJsonStringifierObjectKeyResult::kChangeEncoding) {
2850  stack_.emplace_back(
2851  ContinuationRecord::ForJSObjectResume<fast_iterable_state>(
2852  obj, descriptor_idx + 1, nof_descriptors,
2853  in_object_properties, in_object_properties_start,
2854  descriptors));
2855  if (IsJSObject(property)) {
2856  stack_.emplace_back(ContinuationRecord::ForJSObject(property));
2857  } else if (IsJSArray(property)) {
2858  stack_.emplace_back(ContinuationRecord::ForJSArray(property));
2859  } else {
2860  stack_.emplace_back(
2861  ContinuationRecord::ForSimpleObject(property));
2862  }
2863  stack_.emplace_back(
2864  ContinuationRecord::ForObjectKey(key_name, comma));
2865  return CHANGE_ENCODING;
2866  }
2867  } else {
2868  DCHECK_NE(key_result,

3406  block += index + 1;

3408  block -= stride;
