3428  SrcChar c = chars[i];
3429  if (V8_LIKELY(DoNotEscape(c))) continue;
3430  needs_escaping = true;
3431  if (sizeof(SrcChar) != 1 && base::IsInRange(c, static_cast<SrcChar>(0xD800),
3432  static_cast<SrcChar>(0xDFFF))) {
3433  // The current character is a surrogate.
3434  buffer_.Append(chars + uncopied_src_index, i - uncopied_src_index);
3435  char double_to_radix_chars[kDoubleToRadixMaxChars];
3436  base::Vector<char> double_to_radix_buffer =
3437  base::ArrayVector(double_to_radix_chars);
3438  if (c <= 0xDBFF) {
3439  // The current character is a leading surrogate.
3440  if (i + 1 < length) {
3441  // There is a next character.
3442  SrcChar next = chars[i + 1];
3443  if (base::IsInRange(next, static_cast<SrcChar>(0xDC00),
3444  static_cast<SrcChar>(0xDFFF))) {
3445  // The next character is a trailing surrogate, meaning this is a
3446  // surrogate pair.
3447  AppendCharacterUnchecked(c);
3448  AppendCharacterUnchecked(next);
3449  i++;
3450  } else {
3451  // The next character is not a trailing surrogate. Thus, the
3452  // current character is a lone leading surrogate.
3453  AppendCStringLiteralUnchecked("\\u");
3454  std::string_view hex =
3455  DoubleToRadixStringView(c, 16, double_to_radix_buffer);
3456  AppendStringUnchecked(hex);
3457  }
3458  } else {
3459  // There is no next character. Thus, the current character is a lone
3460  // leading surrogate.
3461  AppendCStringLiteralUnchecked("\\u");
3462  std::string_view hex =
3463  DoubleToRadixStringView(c, 16, double_to_radix_buffer);
3464  AppendStringUnchecked(hex);
3465  }
3466  } else {
3467  // The current character is a lone trailing surrogate. (If it had been
3468  // preceded by a leading surrogate, we would've ended up in the other
3469  // branch earlier on, and the current character would've been handled
3470  // as part of the surrogate pair already.)
3471  AppendCStringLiteralUnchecked("\\u");
3472  std::string_view hex =
3473  DoubleToRadixStringView(c, 16, double_to_radix_buffer);
3474  AppendStringUnchecked(hex);
3475  }
3476  uncopied_src_index = i + 1;
3477  } else {
3478  buffer_.Append(chars + uncopied_src_index, i - uncopied_src_index);
3479  DCHECK_LT(c, 0x60);
3480  AppendCStringUnchecked(&JsonEscapeTable[c * kJsonEscapeTableEntrySize]);
3481  uncopied_src_index = i + 1;
3482  }
3483  }
3484  if (uncopied_src_index < length) {
3485  buffer_.Append(chars + uncopied_src_index, length - uncopied_src_index);
3486  }
3487  return needs_escaping;
3488 }

3492 bool CanUseFastStringifier(DirectHandle<JSAny> replacer,
3493  DirectHandle<Object> gap) {
3494  // TODO(pthier): Support gap on fast-path.
3495  return v8_flags.json_stringify_fast_path && IsUndefined(*replacer) &&
3496  IsUndefined(*gap);

3499 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> FastJsonStringify(Isolate* isolate,
3500  Handle<JSAny> object) {
3501  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3502 
3503  FastJsonStringifier<uint8_t> one_byte_stringifier(isolate);
3504  std::optional<FastJsonStringifier<base::uc16>> two_byte_stringifier;
3505  FastJsonStringifierResult result =
3506  one_byte_stringifier.SerializeObject(*object, no_gc);
3507  bool result_is_one_byte = true;
3508 
3509  if (result == CHANGE_ENCODING) {
3510  two_byte_stringifier.emplace(isolate);
3511  result = two_byte_stringifier->ResumeFrom(one_byte_stringifier, no_gc);
3512  DCHECK_NE(result, CHANGE_ENCODING);
3513  result_is_one_byte = false;
3514  }
3515 
3516  if (V8_LIKELY(result == SUCCESS)) {
3517  if (result_is_one_byte) {
3518  const size_t length = one_byte_stringifier.ResultLength();
3519  DirectHandle<SeqOneByteString> ret;
3520  {
3521  AllowGarbageCollection allow_gc;
3522  if (length > String::kMaxLength) {
3523  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewInvalidStringLengthError());
3524  }
3525  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
3526  isolate, ret,
3527  isolate->factory()->NewRawOneByteString(static_cast<int>(length)));
3528  }
3529  one_byte_stringifier.CopyResultTo(ret->GetChars(no_gc));
3530  return ret;
3531  } else {
3532  DCHECK(two_byte_stringifier.has_value());
3533  const size_t one_byte_length = one_byte_stringifier.ResultLength();
3534  const size_t two_byte_length = two_byte_stringifier->ResultLength();
3535  const size_t total_length = one_byte_length + two_byte_length;
3536  DirectHandle<SeqTwoByteString> ret;
3537  {
3538  AllowGarbageCollection allow_gc;
3539  if (total_length > String::kMaxLength) {
3540  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewInvalidStringLengthError());
3541  }
3542  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, ret,
3543  isolate->factory()->NewRawTwoByteString(
3544  static_cast<int>(total_length)));
3545  }
3546  base::uc16* chars = ret->GetChars(no_gc);
3547  if (one_byte_length > 0) {
3548  one_byte_stringifier.CopyResultTo(chars);
3549  }
3550  DCHECK_GT(two_byte_length, 0);
3551  two_byte_stringifier->CopyResultTo(chars + one_byte_length);
3552  return ret;
3553  }
3554  } else if (result == UNDEFINED) {
3555  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
3556  } else if (result == SLOW_PATH) {
3557  // TODO(pthier): Resume instead of restarting.
3558  AllowGarbageCollection allow_gc;
3559  JsonStringifier stringifier(isolate);
3560  Handle<JSAny> undefined = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
3561  return stringifier.Stringify(object, undefined, undefined);
3562  }
3563  DCHECK(result == EXCEPTION);
3564  CHECK(isolate->has_exception());
3565  return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>();
3566 }

3570 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> JsonStringify(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSAny> object,

3572  Handle<Object> gap) {
3573  if (CanUseFastStringifier(replacer, gap)) {
3574  return FastJsonStringify(isolate, object);
3575  } else {
3576  JsonStringifier stringifier(isolate);
3577  return stringifier.Stringify(object, replacer, gap);
3578  }
3579 }
